  <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$b" id="aspace_cd8a2e6c079b824c91c285c5a3cbf5f7">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection is comprised of diaries, typescripts, correspondence, artifacts, and published journals. The bulk of the collection is formed by the typescripts of <emph render='italic'>How It Happened That I Came to Live in the West</emph>. The Correspondence series also relates to this novel. Diaries date from LittleDog's teenage years in Germany, a red Hofner accordion belonged to LittleDog's father. Dates range from 1954-1984. Books and periodicals cataloged separately.</p>  </scopecontent>
